Author-Name:   Suri, Rajneesh
Author-Name:  Monroe, Kent B
Title: 
 The Effects of Time Constraints on Consumers' Judgments of Prices and Products.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 92-104
Issue: 1
Volume: 30
Year: 2003
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 This article examines how time constraints influence consumers' product
 evaluations over different levels of price information. To understand the
 effects of time constraints (time pressure), a conceptual framework
 incorporating both the motivational and the resource effects of time
 constraints on consumers' information processing is developed. Using price
 as the attribute information to be evaluated, specific hypotheses about
 the effects of time constraints on the relationship between price and
 consumers' perceptions of quality and monetary sacrifice are proposed. The
 results of a replicated experiment show that perceptions of quality and
 monetary sacrifice exhibit different response patterns depending on the
 time constraints, price levels, and subjects' motivations to process
 information. Additional analyses provide insights into how these two
 perceptions are integrated to form perceptions of value.


